### Dictionary<TKey, TValue> in C#

Dictionary stores key-value pairs for fast lookup by key. Keys must be unique.

### Creating Dictionaries

```csharp
Dictionary<string, int> ages = new Dictionary<string, int>();
var scores = new Dictionary<string, int>
{
    { "Alice", 95 },
    { "Bob", 87 },
    { "Charlie", 92 }
};

// Target-typed (C# 9+)
Dictionary<string, int> map = new();
```

### Adding and Accessing

```csharp
var dict = new Dictionary<string, int>();

// Add
dict.Add("Alice", 30);
dict["Bob"] = 25;  // Add or update

// Access
int age = dict["Alice"];     // Throws if key not found
bool exists = dict.TryGetValue("Bob", out int bobAge);  // Safe access
```

### Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Unique keys | Each key must be unique |
| Fast lookup | O(1) average time complexity |
| Ordered | Insertion order NOT preserved (use OrderedDictionary) |
| Key types | Any type with GetHashCode() and Equals() |

### Checking Keys

```csharp
if (dict.ContainsKey("Alice"))
    Console.WriteLine($"Alice is {dict["Alice"]}");

if (dict.ContainsValue(95))
    Console.WriteLine("Someone scored 95");
```

### Iterating

```csharp
foreach (var kvp in dict)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"{kvp.Key}: {kvp.Value}");
}

// Keys only
foreach (var key in dict.Keys) { }

// Values only
foreach (var value in dict.Values) { }
```

### Removing

```csharp
dict.Remove("Bob");        // Remove by key
dict.Clear();               // Remove all
```

### Common Methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Add(key, value)` | Adds key-value pair |
| `TryGetValue(key, out value)` | Safe value retrieval |
| `ContainsKey(key)` | Checks if key exists |
| `Remove(key)` | Removes by key |
| `TryAdd(key, value)` | Adds if key doesn't exist |
| `EnsureCapacity(capacity)` | Pre-allocates |
| `TrimExcess()` | Reduces capacity |

### Alternative Dictionary Types

```csharp
SortedList<TKey, TValue>   // Sorted by key
SortedDictionary<TKey, TValue>  // Sorted with tree
OrderedDictionary           // Preserves insertion order (.NET 9+)
ConcurrentDictionary<TKey, TValue>  // Thread-safe
```

> **Key Point:** Dictionaries provide fast O(1) key-based lookups. Keys must be unique and implement GetHashCode/Equals. Use `TryGetValue` for safe access instead of catching exceptions. Iterate with `KeyValuePair<TKey, TValue>`.

### Custom Key Types

```csharp
public record Person(string Name, int Age);

var dict = new Dictionary<Person, string>();
// Records have built-in HashCode and Equals
```

### Dictionary with Default Value

```csharp
// C# 8.0+ pattern
var value = dict.TryGetValue(key, out var val) ? val : defaultValue;

// Using GetValueOrDefault extension
var value = dict.GetValueOrDefault(key, defaultValue);
```

codeExample:
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        var inventory = new Dictionary<string, int>
        {
            ["Apples"] = 50,
            ["Bananas"] = 30,
            ["Cherries"] = 20
        };

        Console.WriteLine("Inventory:");
        foreach (var item in inventory)
            Console.WriteLine($"{item.Key}: {item.Value}");

        // Lookup
        if (inventory.TryGetValue("Apples", out int count))
            Console.WriteLine($"\nApples in stock: {count}");

        // Update
        inventory["Apples"] = 45;
        Console.WriteLine($"After update: {inventory["Apples"]}");
    }
}
